te kind-load-all aggregate target\n92:   - Add `.PHONY: kind-load-all`\n93:   - Set dependency on all three load targets\n94:   - Add success message\n95:   - File: `Makefile`\n96:   - Verify: `make kind-load-all` loads all images\n97: \n98: - [ ] **T3.2** Create kind-load-workloadmanager target\n99:   - Add `.PHONY: kind-load-workloadmanager`\n100:   - Run `kind load docker-image $(WORKLOADMANAGER_IMAGE):$(DOCKER_TAG)`\n101:   - File: `Makefile`\n102:   - Verify: Image loaded to Kind cluster\n103: \n104: - [ ] **T3.3** Create kind-load-router target\n105:   - Add `.PHONY: kind-load-router`\n106:   - Run `kind load docker-image $(ROUTER_IMAGE):$(DOCKER_TAG)`\n107:   - File: `Makefile`\n108:   - Verify: Image loaded to Kind cluster\n109: \n110: - [ ] **T3.4** Create kind-load-picod target\n111:   - Add `.PHONY: kind-load-picod`\n112:   - Run `kind load docker-image $(PICOD_IMAGE):$(DOCKER_TAG)`\n113:   - File: `Makefile`\n114:   - Verify: Image loaded to Kind cluster\n115: \n116: ---\n117: \n118: ## Phase 4: Multi-Architecture Build Targets\n119: \n120: - [ ] **T4.1** Create docker-buildx-all aggregate target\n121:   - Add `.PHONY: docker-buildx-all`\n122:   - Set dependency on all three buildx targets\n123:   - Add success message\n124:   - File: `Makefile`\n125:   - Verify: `make docker-buildx-all` builds all multi-arch images\n126: \n127: - [ ] **T4.2** Create docker-buildx-workloadmanager target\n128:   - Add `.PHONY: docker-buildx-workloadmanager`\n129:   - Build with `--platform linux/amd64,linux/arm64`\n130:   - Use `-f deployment/docker/Dockerfile`\n131:   - Add `--push` flag\n132:   - File: `Makefile`\n133:   - Verify: Multi-arch image built and pushed\n134: \n135: - [ ] **T4.3** Create docker-buildx-router target\n136:   - Add `.PHONY: docker-buildx-router`\n137:   - Build with `--platform linux/amd64,linux/arm64`\n138:   - Use `-f deployment/docker/Dockerfile.router`\n139:   - Add `--push` flag\n140:   - File: `Makefile`\n141:   - Verify: Multi-arch image built and pushed\n142: \n143: - [ ] **T4.4** Create docker-buildx-picod target\n144:   - Add `.PHONY: docker-buildx-picod`\n145:   - Build with `--platform linux/amd64,linux/arm64`\n146:   - Use `-f deployment/docker/Dockerfile.picod`\n147:   - Add `--push` flag\n148:   - File: `Makefile`\n149:   - Verify: Multi-arch image built and pushed\n150: \n151: ---\n152: \n153: ## Phase 5: Cleanup Target\n154: \n155: - [ ] **T5.1** Create docker-clean target\n156:   - Add `.PHONY: docker-clean`\n157:   - Remove all three images with all tags\n158:   - Use `-` prefix on docker rmi commands to ignore errors\n159:   - Use `|| true` for graceful failure\n160:   - File: `Makefile`\n161:   - Verify: `make docker-clean` removes images safely\n162: \n163: ---\n164: \n165: ## Phase 6: Validation Targets\n166: \n167: - [ ] **T6.1** Create docker-validate aggregate target\n168:   - Add `.PHONY: docker-validate`\n169:   - Set dependency on all three validate targets\n170:   - Add success message\n171:   - File: `Makefile`\n172:   - Verify: `make docker-validate` validates all images\n173: \n174: - [ ] **T6.2** Create docker-validate-workloadmanager target\n175:   - Add `.PHONY: docker-validate-workloadmanager`\n176:   - Run `./deployment/docker/test/validate.sh` with image name\n177:   - File: `Makefile`\n178:   - Verify: Validation script executed\n179: \n180: - [ ] **T6.3** Create docker-validate-router target\n181:   - Add `.PHONY: docker-validate-router`\n182:   - Run `./deployment/docker/test/validate.sh` with image name\n183:   - File: `Makefile`\n184:   - Verify: Validation script executed\n185: \n186: - [ ] **T6.4** Create docker-validate-picod target\n187:   - Add `.PHONY: docker-validate-picod`\n188:   - Run `./deployment/docker/test/validate.sh` with image name\n189:   - File: `Makefile`\n190:   - Verify: Validation script executed\n191: \n192: ---\n193: \n194: ## Phase 7: Test Targets\n195: \n196: - [ ] **T7.1** Create docker-test aggregate target\n197:   - Add `.PHONY: docker-test`\n198:   - Set dependency on `docker-test-build` and `docker-test-runtime`\n199:   - Add success message\n200:   - File: `Makefile`\n201:   - Verify: `make docker-test` runs all tests\n202: \n203: - [ ] **T7.2** Create docker-test-build target\n204:   - Add `.PHONY: docker-test-build`\n205:   - Run `./deployment/docker/test/build_test.sh`\n206:   - File: `Makefile`\n207:   - Verify: Build tests executed\n208: \n209: - [ ] **T7.3** Create docker-test-runtime target\n210:   - Add `.PHONY: docker-test-runtime`\n211:   - Run `./deployment/docker/test/runtime_test.sh`\n212:   - File: `Makefile`\n213:   - Verify: Runtime tests executed\n214: \n215: ---\n216: \n217: ## Phase 8: Help Target\n218: \n219: - [ ] **T8.1** Create help target with build targets documentation\n220:   - Add `.PHONY: help`\n221:   - Print \"AgentCube Docker Makefile\" header\n222:   - Print \"Build targets:\" section with descriptions\n223:   - File: `Makefile`\n224:   - Verify: Help shows build targets\n225: \n226: - [ ] **T8.2** Add push targets documentation to help\n227:   - Print \"Push targets:\" section with descriptions\n228:   - File: `Makefile`\n229:   - Verify: Help shows push targets\n230: \n231: - [ ] **T8.3** Add Kind targets documentation to help\n232:   - Print \"Kind targets:\" section with descriptions\n233:   - File: `Makefile`\n234:   - Verify: Help shows Kind targets\n235: \n236: - [ ] **T8.4** Add multi-arch targets documentation to help\n237:   - Print \"Multi-arch targets:\" section with descriptions\n238:   - File: `Makefile`\n239:   - Verify: Help shows multi-arch targets\n240: \n241: - [ ] **T8.5** Add test & validate targets documentation to help\n242:   - Print \"Test & validate targets:\" section with descriptions\n243:   - File: `Makefile`\n244:   - Verify: Help shows test and validate targets\n245: \n246: - [ ] **T8.6** Add variables documentation to help\n247:   - Print \"Variables:\" section with current values\n248:   - Show `DOCKER_REGISTRY`, `DOCKER_TAG`,