e docker-clean`\n302:   - Verify: Images removed (errors ignored if not present)\n303: \n304: - [ ] **T10.5** Test help target\n305:   - Command: `make help`\n306:   - Verify: All targets documented with correct descriptions\n307:   - Verify: Variable values displayed\n308: \n309: - [ ] **T10.6** Test individual build targets\n310:   - Command: `make docker-build-workloadmanager`\n311:   - Command: `make docker-build-router`\n312:   - Command: `make docker-build-picod`\n313:   - Verify: Each builds independently\n314: \n315: - [ ] **T10.7** Test individual push targets (dry-run or skip if no registry)\n316:   - Verify: Push targets have correct image references\n317:   - Verify: Push targets use all three tags\n318: \n319: ---\n320: \n321: ## Acceptance Criteria\n322: \n323: 1. ✅ `DOCKER_REGISTRY`, `DOCKER_TAG`, `VERSION`, `COMMIT_SHA` variables defined\n324: 2. ✅ Image name variables for all three components defined\n325: 3. ✅ `docker-build-all` builds all three images sequentially\n326: 4. ✅ Individual build targets for each component exist\n327: 5. ✅ All build targets tag images with DOCKER_TAG, COMMIT_SHA, VERSION\n328: 6. ✅ `docker-push-all` pushes all images to registry\n329: 7. ✅ Individual push targets push all three tags\n330: 8. ✅ `kind-load-all` loads all images to Kind cluster\n331: 9. ✅ Individual kind-load targets exist for each component\n332: 10. ✅ `docker-buildx-all` builds multi-arch images (amd64, arm64)\n333: 11. ✅ Multi-arch build targets use `--push` flag\n334: 12. ✅ `docker-clean` safely removes local images\n335: 13. ✅ `docker-validate` validates all images\n336: 14. ✅ `docker-test` runs build and runtime tests\n337: 15. ✅ `make help` displays all targets with descriptions\n338: 16. ✅ Help shows current variable values\n339: 17. ✅ All targets declared as `.PHONY`\n340: 18. ✅ All recipe lines use tab indentation\n341: 19. ✅ Consistent echo messages for user feedback\n342: 20. ✅ Targets organized in logical groups\n343: 21. ✅ No hardcoded image